CNCP v1 23736
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8553: Allow components passed as slot prop to be used in the slot",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:20.048718+00:00",
  "text": "Allow components passed as slot prop to be used in the slot\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <SomeComponent v-slot=\"{ SpecializedComponent }\">\r\n    <SpecializedComponent />\r\n  </SomeComponent>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAt the moment, vue does not consider components passed as slot property on render. Instead it complains about \"SpecializedComponent\" being unknown.\r\n\r\nWhy is this useful:\r\n\r\n1. Allow to render parent-child relationships in an easy way:\r\n\r\nThis basically allows to wrap the inner content of a parent component with some custom styling or whatnot.\r\nA similar concept is used in vue-router to display the current page (`<router-view>`)\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <Table>\r\n    <template #td=\"{ Child }\">\r\n      <td style=\"background: red\">\r\n        <Child />\r\n      </td\r\n    </template>\r\n  </Table>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Allow typed components that rely on props passed to the parent component\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <Table :data=\"typedData\" v-slot=\"{ Column }\">\r\n    <Column prop=\"willErrorWithWrongKey\" />\r\n    <Column v-slot=\"{ row }\">\r\n      {{ row.typedProperties }}\r\n    </Column>\r\n  </Table>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\nBoth cases are extremely useful for different reasons\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n\r\nSee above or look at [this playground](https://play.vuejs.org/#eNp9UEsOgjAQvcqkGzcqe1NJiEfQZTcFqpL0F1pwQbi7U1oQMXHVvnbeZ95ACmuPfSfIiVBXtY314ITvbM50o6xpPdx4KQXcW6Ngd8wmFAg7pmkWGTiLwAtlJfcCEQCNrP7gpPFnRga4GNkpDSMj0wCOpJcsEqIy3mm2KJE9WfxCwJUF87Ru+iR1NUqknKXEgyeHYI4ZykbXmwyLaxT5ckWwbgIk1w+kezdFT60kqbmWCLe9YP7Px+8CznKdF1BFqRd38BStQHZ430T6HyrsEreYncc3fKKirQ==)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
